name: Set Node Mapping
info:
Input is a message
Output is same message, with display_key set to "{app_id}.{dev_id}" and display_name set to a friendly name from the built-in map.

name: Map devID to friendy name
Catena Port 1 fmt 0x20 Message Decoder (4630 PMS7003)
info:
Output port 1 is the complete data set, in a normal object form. Dewpoint, heatindex, and normalized pressure have been added.

Output port 2 is the interesting application data, split into the fields and tags required by influxdb. Timestamp is not supplied, so InfluxDB will tag the data with the arrival time at the database.

Output port 3 is the RF-related data, split into fields plus tags, suitable for injection into the RF daatabase.

name: Prepare for DataBase
Decode data (port 1 format 20)
Add normalized pressure
Prep for RF store
